President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has ordered that the flag of the United States be flown at half-staff to honor the victims of the recent shooting at Robb Elementary School in Uvalde, Texas. This order applies to the White House, public buildings and grounds, military posts and naval stations, and naval vessels of the Federal Government in Washington, D.C., and across the United States and its Territories and possessions until sunset on May 28, 2022. The flag will also be flown at half-staff for the same duration at all United States embassies, legations, consular offices, and other facilities abroad, including military facilities and naval vessels and stations. The President signed this order on May 24, 2022.